ence? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{3}":[53,54],"#2) Write your own opinion why you as a student of IT-University should/shouldn’t learn/study the second order theory of real numbers? What do you think about a need of theory of limits in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science, Robotics, and/or Data Science? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{4}":[55,55],"#2) Write your own opinion why you as a student of IT-University should/shouldn’t learn/study the second order theory of real numbers? What do you think about a need of theory of limits in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science, Robotics, and/or Data Science? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{5}":[56,58],"#2) Write your own opinion why you as a student of IT-University should/shouldn’t learn/study the second order theory of real numbers? What do you think about a need of theory of limits in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science, Robotics, and/or Data Science? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{6}":[59,59],"#2) Write your own opinion why you as a student of IT-University should/shouldn’t learn/study the second order theory of real numbers? What do you think about a need of theory of limits in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science, Robotics, and/or Data Science? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{7}":[60,60],"#2) Write your own opinion why you as a student of IT-University should/shouldn’t learn/study the second order theory of real numbers? What do you think about a need of theory of limits in IT, Software Engineering, Computer Science, Robotics, and/or Data Science? – Proof a need by example(s) but refute a need with a comprehensive proof.#{8}":[61,61],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.":[62,136],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#{1}":[63,63],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#What is Naive Set Theory and Why do we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis?":[64,68],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#What is Naive Set Theory and Why do we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis?#{1}":[66,68],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#2-3 Postulates of Naive Set Theory:":[69,78],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#2-3 Postulates of Naive Set Theory:#{1}":[71,78],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?":[79,98],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#{1}":[81,82],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:":[83,98],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:#{1}":[85,88],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:#{2}":[89,89],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:#{3}":[90,91],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:#{4}":[92,95],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Is any collection a set in Naive Set Theory?#The Rassell's Paradox:#{5}":[96,98],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Proof: Union and Intersection of Three Sets is a Set":[99,113],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Proof: Union and Intersection of Three Sets is a Set#{1}":[101,113],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Cartesian Product of two sets is a set:":[114,121],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Cartesian Product of two sets is a set:#{1}":[116,121],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Cartesian Product of Finite Sets":[122,130],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Cartesian Product of Finite Sets#{1}":[124,130],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Conclusion:":[131,136],"#3) What is naïve set theory and why we need to learn it in Mathematical Analysis? Could you please present 2-3 its postulates and explain? Is any collection a set (according to the naïve set theory)? Prove that union and intersection of any three sets is a set again. Can you prove that Cartesian product of any two sets is a set too? – If you cannot, then try to prove that Cartesian product of any two finite sets is a set.#Conclusion:#{1}":[133,136],"#4) Construct the set representation for natural numbers $0,1,2,3$ and prove by construction that these representations are sets indeed. Prove that set-theoretic representation $S$ of your individual number $M$ is a set indeed. What is cardinality of $S$? What is cardinality of $2^S$?":[137,190],"#4) Construct the set representation for natural numbers $0,1,2,3$ and prove by construction that these representations are sets indeed. Prove that set-theoretic representation $S$ of your individual number $M$ is a set indeed. What is cardinality of $S$? What is cardinality of $2^S$?#{1}":[138,138],"#4) Construct the set representation for natural numbers $0,1,2,3$ and prove by construction that these representations are sets indeed. Prove that set-theoretic representation $S$ of your individual number $M$ is a set indeed. What is cardinality of $S$? What is cardinality of $2^S$?#Set-Theoretic Representation of Natural Numbers":[139,164],"#4) Construct the set representation for natural numbers $0,1,2,3$ and prove by construction that these representations are sets indeed. Prove that set-theoretic representation $S$ of your individual number $M$ is a set indeed. What is cardinality of $S$? What is cardinality of $2^S$?#Set-Theoretic Representation of Natural Numbers#{1}":[141,145],"#4) Construct the set representation for natural numbers $0,1,2,3$ and prove by construction that these representations are sets indeed. Prove that set-